\subsection*{12.3 Grouped Data}

\subsection*{12.3.1 Frequency Distributions}

When summarising large masses of raw data it is often useful to distribute the data into classes or categories and to determine the number of individuals belonging to each class, called the class frequency. A tabular arrangement of these data by classes together with the corresponding class frequencies is called a frequency distribution or frequency table. The table below shows a frequency distribution of weights (recorded to the nearest kg ) $2 \times 100$ male students at Informatics Computer School.
